  "instructions": [
    "Combine 1 cup of warm water and yeast in a large bowl. Let it sit for 5 minutes until frothy.",
    "Add sugar, salt, and yeast mixture to the flour mixture. Mix until a dough forms.",
    "Knead the dough for 5-7 minutes until smooth and elastic.",
    "Cover the dough with a damp cloth and let it rest for 1 hour in a warm place.",
    "Divide the dough into 4 equal parts. Roll out each part into a thin circle.",
    "Heat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat. Cook each paratha for 1-2 minutes on each side until golden brown.",
    "Brush the paratha with ghee or oil and sprinkle with ground cardomom, mustard seeds, and ferment-jang.",
    "Repeat with the remaining dough portions.",
    "Serve warm and enjoy!"
  ],
